reviews.text:
Since hearing about this on the Noted episode, I've been waiting for you to release the recipe. I'm writing this review 12 days after mixing, so it's probably going to change a little. This is my first time using Pandoro (had the ingredient for a good 6 months), so I don't have any recipes to compare the use of this ingredient to.  As far as the recipe goes, it's very good. You definitely get lemon in this recipe. It hits you in the face the first couple pulls, then it calms down and it's not overpowering. The frosting is present, but I think can be a little heavier to separate it from the cupcake (this may change with a longer steep). I wouldn't change anything with the cream filling nor cupcake. Overall, it's a very good recipe. The only thing I would tweak is the frosting. Adding a sweeter lemon might help the frosting, but I might be wrong. Maybe adding some FE Lemon might help this. &#xD;
&#xD;
I rate this a 4.25 / 5.00 &#xD;
&#xD;
Thank you for the share!
